						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the Basavaṇṇa temple about a mile from the village.</p>						

						<p>Circa 18th century.</p>						

						<p>It seems to describe the glory of Basavaṇṇa (i.e., Bull-god) and some miracle attributed to Him.</p>						

						</summary>
